-- Shire up on market talk of Pfizer interest: traders
-- 
-- Fri Mar 14, 2008 5:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/14/us-shire-shares-idUSL1428044820080314

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Shares in drug maker Shire ( SHP.L ) rose as much as 4.8 percent on Friday as traders cited market talk of bid interest from U.S. rival Pfizer ( PFE.N ). 

 Shire declined to comment. By 5:37 a.m. EDT, Shire shares were up 4 percent at 981.5 pence ($1.99). More than two million shares changed hands in the first 100 minutes of trade, compared with a daily average of 6.5 million shares in the past 30 days. (Additional reporting by  Mark Potter ) (Reporting by  Dominic Lau )